  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Legislation\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Laws\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) statutes\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n- Patriot Act provisions\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Financial penalties\n- Regulatory sanctions\n\n5. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Banking regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Judicial systems\n\n6. Typical Offenses\n- Concealing illegal financial transactions\n- Structuring transactions to avoid reporting\n- Transferring illicit funds\n- Integrating criminal proceeds into legitimate financial systems\n\n7. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Professional disqualification\n- Organizational sanctions\n\nThis framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
